插.definition: to insert; stick in; pierce; to take part in; to interfere; to interpose

插上.definition: to plug into; to insert; to stick in

插件.definition: plug-in (software or hardware); to plug in a component

插入.definition: to insert; to stick in; to plug in

插卡式.definition: (of a device, e.g. public telephone, ticket inspection machine) designed to have a card or ticket inserted

插口.definition: socket (for an electric plug); to interrupt (sb speaking); to butt in

插嘴.definition: to interrupt (sb talking); to butt in; to cut into a conversation

插手.definition: to get involved in; to meddle; interference

插播.definition: to interrupt (a radio or TV program) with a commercial insert, breaking news etc; to put a call on hold

插播廣告.definition: slot advertisement; interstitial ad; splash ad

插曲.definition: music played during a movie, play etc; incidental music; music played in a theatrical interlude; (fig.) incident; episode

插班.definition: to join a class partway through the course

插眼.definition: to poke in the eye; (gaming) to place a ward (i.e. vision-granting item); to keep tabs on (an online discussion etc); to monitor (for updates)

插科打諢.definition: to include impromptu comic material in opera performance (idiom); to jest; buffoonery

插線板.definition: power strip; powerboard (with multiple electrical sockets)

插翅難飛.definition: lit. even given wings, you couldn't fly (idiom); fig. impossible to escape

插腳.definition: to shove in; to edge in; fig. to poke one's nose into people's business; prong

插足.definition: to squeeze in; to step in; to take part; to step between (two persons in a relationship)

插進.definition: to insert; to stick in; to plug in (an electronic device)

插銷.definition: bolt (for locking a window, cabinet etc); (electrical) plug

插隊.definition: to cut in line; to jump a queue; to live on a rural community (during the Cultural Revolution)
